backlogItems.name: Admin marks pending photos to Approve/Deny
backlogItems.description:
User Story Title: Admin evaluates pending photos

	As an Administrator
	I can view all pending photos, paginated
	So that I can evaluate them and mark them for approval or denial
	
	Acceptance Criteria 1: 
	
	Given that there are pending photos
	When the admin clicks on “View Pending Photos”
	Then display photos, one per row, with “Approve” and “Deny” checkboxes, and a box to select or enter a reason for Denial that is enabled when the Deny checkbox is checked.
	   And the admin chooses “Cancel” or “Save” to go back to main screen

	Acceptance Criteria 2: 

	Given that some photos are valid
	When the admin evaluates them
	Then the admin checks “Approve” on the appropriate photos
	   And then clicks “Save” 
              And the students are notified of their photo’s approval
	   And the admin is taken back to the main screen

	Acceptance Criteria 3:
	
	Given that some photos are invalid
	When the admin evaluates them
	Then the admin checks “Deny” on the appropriate photos
	   And the admin enters a reason for denial in the box that appears
	   And then clicks “Save” 
              And the students are notified of their photo’s denial
	   And the admin is taken back to the main screen

	Acceptance Criteria 4:
	
	Given the admin closes the window before saving their checkbox selections
	When evaluating pending photos
	Then the selections do not take effect
	   And the admin must start over the next time they view pending photos

tasks.name: Write client-side code that sends approve/deny updates on "Save"
tasks.description:
This will be a Javascript function that:
1. Reads the form elements of the pending photos
2. marks if they are either approved or denied, and saves the reasons for denIal (if applicable)
3. sends an array with this data to the server (via a Javascript request) when the Admin hits the "Save" button.

tasks.name: Write server-side code that handles approve/deny request from Task #1709
tasks.description:
1. Receive incoming request from the client.
2. Update the Photo rows in the database with their new approve/deny status, including the reason for denial if the new status is "deny".
3. Create email task that triggers sending an email with approve or denail notices to the students of the approved/denied photos.
4. Update appropriate Student database rows with a flag that signals they should be shown an approve/deny message (determined by the status of their most recently uploaded photo).
5. Send success/failure response to the client

tasks.name: Handle success/failure of response to the approve/deny request
tasks.description:
1. Accept and process the returned response from the approve/deny request.

2. Add UI that displays "success" or "failure" message depending on the response status.
